Zenconomy:
Have the same issue with $cordovaFile.readAsDataURL

As a temporary fix, I monkey-patched ng-cordova.js, thanks a million for the tip.

```
// From
$window.requestFileSystem($window.PERSISTENT, 1024 * 1024, q.resolve, q.reject);

// To
$window.requestFileSystem(4, 1024 * 1024, q.resolve, q.reject);
```

I also had to pass the local file name only, passing the full path resulted in an error. Not sure if this is a bug or just inconsistent behavior.

```
// Passing the full path does not work
$cordovaFile.readAsDataURL(cordova.file.dataDirectory + 'test.jpg') 

// But this works
$cordovaFile.readAsDataURL('test.jpg')
```
. @panchisco we completely stopped using ngCordova for anything related to the file system as there are several serious bugs and limitations in their implementation.

Instead we're just using the native cordova commands, I recommend you do the same... it will save you a lot of pain and frustration.
