AdamVig:
As I understand it, the appropriate way to handle these types of errors is to wrap your calls for Cordova functions in conditionals that check for the Cordova plugin's existence:

```
if (window.cordova && window.cordova.plugins.Keyboard) {
    // Do something
}
```

I agree that it would be cool to have a preprocessor to handle this for you, but in the meantime, this is the way I have been dealing with it.
