. The main difference is that you have to pass in an `options` object to the `initialize` method first.  Then you can call `register` to get a registration id.

``` js
var options = {
        "android": { "senderID": "12345" },
        "ios": { "alert": true, "badge": true, "sound": true }
      };
$cordovaPush.initialize(options);
```

Now you can do this: 

``` js

$cordovaPush.register().then( (regId) => {
    console.log('Registration ID: ', regId);
});
```
