DanielBertocci:
I made a mistake, I pulled #1087
. I chose callback solution for backward compatibility.
I think the following solution is better:

``` javascript
openDB: function (options, background) {
    var q = $q.defer();
    if (angular.isObject(options) && !angular.isString(options)) {
        if (typeof background !== 'undefined') {
            options.bgType = background;
        }
    }
    else {
        options = {
            name: options,
            bgType: background
        };
    }
    $window.sqlitePlugin.openDatabase(options, q.resolve, q.reject);
    return q.promise;
}
```

In this way, openDB returns a promise and forces the developer to use `.then(success,error)`.
It can be done, but it is different from the older version.
